12. Specific Information About Twilio 2FA

12.1 How Twilio 2FA Works

When you enable two-factor authentication via SMS:

1.
You provide your phone number during account setup

2.
When you log in, we send a verification code via Twilio

3.
You enter the code to complete authentication

4.
The code is verified and your session is established

12.2 Phone Number Usage

•
Your phone number is used exclusively for sending verification codes

•
We do not use your phone number for marketing or other purposes

•
Your phone number is not shared with any third parties except Twilio

•
You can remove your phone number and disable 2FA at any time

12.3 SMS Message Privacy

•
SMS messages are sent by Twilio on our behalf

•
Message content is limited to verification codes

•
Messages are not stored on our servers after delivery

•
Twilio may retain logs for security and compliance purposes

12.4 Costs

•
Standard SMS rates may apply depending on your phone carrier

•
We do not charge for 2FA verification

•
Your carrier may charge for receiving SMS messages

12.5 Opting Out

You can disable SMS 2FA at any time from your account settings. However, we recommend keeping 2FA enabled for security.

